Dimension reduction for MNIST dataset

Dense shallow network for classifying MNIST dataset

library(keras)
use_condaenv("r-tensorflow",conda=YOUR.PATH.TO.CONDA)

Download data

mnist <- dataset_mnist()
x_train <- mnist$train$x
y_train <- mnist$train$y
x_test <- mnist$test$x
y_test <- mnist$test$y

Reshape and rescale data

x_train <- array_reshape(x_train, c(nrow(x_train), 784))
x_test <- array_reshape(x_test, c(nrow(x_test), 784))
x_train <- x_train / 255
x_test <- x_test / 255
y_train <- to_categorical(y_train, 10)
y_test <- to_categorical(y_test, 10)

Define dense shallow model

model <- keras_model_sequential() 
model %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 256, activation = 'elu', input_shape = c(784)) %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 10, activation = 'softmax')

Compile and fit the model

model %>% compile(
  loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
  optimizer = optimizer_nadam(),
  metrics = c('accuracy')
)

history <- model %>% fit(
  x_train, y_train, 
  epochs = 30, batch_size = 1000, 
  validation_split = 0.2
)
plot(history)

print(evaluate(model, x_test, y_test))
## $loss
## [1] 0.07900751
## 
## $acc
## [1] 0.9767

PCA

mnist.pca <- princomp(x_train)
x_train.pca <- predict(mnist.pca,x_train)[,1:256]
x_test.pca <- predict(mnist.pca,x_test)[,1:256]
fve <- cumsum(mnist.pca$sdev^2)/sum(mnist.pca$sdev^2)
plot(1:784,fve,type="l")
lines(1:784,rep(0.95,784),col="red")

Define dense shallow model

model <- keras_model_sequential() 
model %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 128, activation = 'elu', input_shape = c(256)) %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 10, activation = 'softmax')

Compile and fit the model

model %>% compile(
  loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
  optimizer = optimizer_nadam(),
  metrics = c('accuracy')
)

history <- model %>% fit(
  x_train.pca, y_train, 
  epochs = 30, batch_size = 1000, 
  validation_split = 0.2
)
plot(history)

print(evaluate(model, x_test.pca, y_test))
## $loss
## [1] 0.08381161
## 
## $acc
## [1] 0.9755

Deep neural networks with linear dimension reduction layer

model <- keras_model_sequential() 
model %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 256, activation = 'linear', input_shape = c(784)) %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 128, activation = 'elu') %>%
  layer_dense(units = 10, activation = 'softmax')
model %>% compile(
  loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
  optimizer = optimizer_nadam(),
  metrics = c('accuracy')
)

history <- model %>% fit(
  x_train, y_train, 
  epochs = 30, batch_size = 1000, 
  validation_split = 0.2
)
plot(history)

print(evaluate(model, x_test, y_test))
## $loss
## [1] 0.09222296
## 
## $acc
## [1] 0.9771

Deep neural networks with nonlinear dimension reduction layer

model <- keras_model_sequential() 
model %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 200, activation = 'elu', input_shape = c(784)) %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 100, activation = 'elu') %>%
  layer_dense(units = 10, activation = 'softmax')
model %>% compile(
  loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
  optimizer = optimizer_nadam(),
  metrics = c('accuracy')
)

history <- model %>% fit(
  x_train, y_train, 
  epochs = 30, batch_size = 1000, 
  validation_split = 0.2
)
plot(history)

print(evaluate(model, x_test, y_test))
## $loss
## [1] 0.08835542
## 
## $acc
## [1] 0.9776
